senses.sense_text:
A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at Jer.36.26; 
only referred to as Hammelech (הַמֶּלֶךְ); 
father of Jerahmeel and Malchijah. § A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at Jer.36.26; 
father of: Jerahmeel (H3396I) and Malchijah (H4441H); also translated "the king";

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, only mentioned at Gen.49.10; 
only referred to as Shiloh (שִׁילֹה). §A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, only mentioned at Gen.49.10; also translated "tribute" 
meaning uncertain
